docs.abstract: Decades of diplomatic efforts to stem global warming have proven ineffectual because too many strategies have been taken off the table.
docs.snippet: Decades of diplomatic efforts to stem global warming have proven ineffectual because too many strategies have been taken off the table.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 1988, when world leaders convened their first global conference on climate change, in Toronto, the Earth’s average temperature was a bit more than half a degree Celsius above the average of the last two decades of the 19th century, according to measurements by NASA.

headline.main: Fighting Climate Change? We’re Not Even Landing a Punch
headline.print_headline: Pulling Punches in Climate Change Fight

keywords.name: subject
keywords.value: United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change

docs.abstract: The former official, Dallas Dance, has been at the center of questions about the relationships between school officials and education technology companies.
docs.snippet: The former official, Dallas Dance, has been at the center of questions about the relationships between school officials and education technology companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: A former superintendent of Baltimore County Public Schools, the 25th-largest district in the United States, pleaded guilty on Thursday to four counts of perjury related to payments totaling about $147,000 that he received for consulting and speaking engagements.

headline.main: Ex-Leader of Baltimore County Schools, a Tech Booster, Pleads Guilty to Perjury
headline.print_headline: In Maryland, a Guilty Plea By a Former Schools Chief

docs.abstract: The 89-year-old, who got his start selling plastic flowers, built his conglomerate just as Hong Kong was becoming a center of capitalism and the entry point into China.
docs.snippet: The 89-year-old, who got his start selling plastic flowers, built his conglomerate just as Hong Kong was becoming a center of capitalism and the entry point into China.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Li Ka-shing, a high school dropout who got his start selling plastic flowers, will retire from the empire that made him Hong Kong’s richest man, he said on Friday, bringing a symbolic end to an era when the road to China’s riches went through the onetime British colony.

headline.main: Li Ka-shing, Hong Kong’s Richest Man, Will Retire, Ending an Era
headline.print_headline: Hong Kong Magnate Plans to Retire, Ending an Era

docs.abstract: Some users reported that Alexa, Amazon’s digital assistant, has been laughing unexpectedly. The behavior is being fixed, the company says.
docs.snippet: Some users reported that Alexa, Amazon’s digital assistant, has been laughing unexpectedly. The behavior is being fixed, the company says.
docs.lead_paragraph: For weeks, users of Amazon’s digital assistant, Alexa, have reported versions of the same unsettling event: being startled as they went about their day by Alexa letting out an eerie laugh.

headline.main: Amazon Knows Why Alexa Was Laughing at Its Customers
headline.print_headline: Amazon Knows Why Alexa Was Laughing at Its Customers (You, Um, Asked for It)

docs.abstract: HBO has signed Ronan Farrow, whose reporting in The New Yorker on Harvey Weinstein helped spur a national discussion on sexual misconduct, to a three-year deal.
docs.snippet: HBO has signed Ronan Farrow, whose reporting in The New Yorker on Harvey Weinstein helped spur a national discussion on sexual misconduct, to a three-year deal.
docs.lead_paragraph: HBO has signed Ronan Farrow to a three-year deal to develop and become the face of a new investigative series, the network announced on Thursday. The deal is set to begin later this year.

headline.main: Ronan Farrow to Develop an Investigative Series for HBO
headline.print_headline: Ronan Farrow Signs 3-Year Deal With HBO

docs.abstract: The hotel business has been going strong in recent years, except in one area: company conferences. But hotel executives are starting to see improvement.
docs.snippet: The hotel business has been going strong in recent years, except in one area: company conferences. But hotel executives are starting to see improvement.
docs.lead_paragraph: The hotel business has been a good one in recent years, as the economy has gathered strength. But there’s one area that’s been lagging — hosting corporate meetings and conferences.

headline.main: Hotels Hope That Tax Law Will Revive Corporate Meetings
headline.print_headline: Rolling Out the Red Carpet For Lower Corporate Taxes

docs.abstract: The Midwest capital city would seem to be a long shot for Amazon’s new headquarters, but its low costs and business-friendly climate might help its chances.
docs.snippet: The Midwest capital city would seem to be a long shot for Amazon’s new headquarters, but its low costs and business-friendly climate might help its chances.

docs.abstract: For decades, watches have been symbols of luxury, wealth and personal taste. But their potential as investments is now more easily tracked and understood.
docs.snippet: For decades, watches have been symbols of luxury, wealth and personal taste. But their potential as investments is now more easily tracked and understood.
docs.lead_paragraph: Like other men with a passion for watches, Cade Mlodinoff began his obsession by coveting one model. It was a Tag Heuer. It cost him $400 when he bought it at age 10.
